    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Corbin Carroll** stands out as the clear centerpiece of the Ghost Ride the WHIP lineup, boasting an elite score of 87.14. Facing a favorable matchup against Martin (xERA 4.68), **Corbin Carroll** benefits from a massive 17% boost due to the SP skill delta and a strong spot in the #3 hole, positioning him as our most reliable engine for R and SB. We are also leaning heavily into the park factor and pitching mismatch against Waldron (xERA 7.83); both **Mickey Moniak** (75.75) and **Kyle Karros** (59.58) capitalize on these conditions. **Mickey Moniak** is particularly attractive, as the combination of park boost and platoon advantage propels him into our top three scorers, even with the inherent volatility of his profile. \n\nStrategic bench decisions continue to prioritize efficiency over chasing raw counting stats. **Brice Turang** (45.53) was the toughest exclusion from the active roster; while he provides the elite SB upside we covet, the brutal matchup against Skubal (xERA 2.71) significantly capped his expected daily value. We opted for the efficiency of **Jose Caballero** (64.17) instead, who leverages a dynamic platoon advantage against Tolle to secure a higher floor. Elsewhere, **Seiya Suzuki** (50.54) remains in the lineup despite a tough draw against S\u00e1nchez, as his score is propped up by favorable wind conditions and his position in the heart of the order, though he remains a risk if the wind shifts or if the catcher's arm negates his aggression on the basepaths. Owners should monitor **James Wood**, whose score of 53.19 is dragged down by a tough matchup against Ritchie, but his lead-off spot remains vital for potential R contribution. **Josh Naylor** is unavailable today, and both **Dalton Rushing** and **Alex Freeland** have been benched, falling below our 40-point efficiency floor against tough opposing arms.",
